definitions.definition: A type of small, sweet -tasting orange, the result of a hybrid cross between the willowleaf variety of mandarin orange ( Citrus × aurantium f. deliciosa ) and a sweet orange ( Citrus sinensis ). Scientific name: Citrus × clementina .

main_definition: A type of small, sweet -tasting orange, the result of a hybrid cross between the willowleaf variety of mandarin orange ( Citrus × aurantium f. deliciosa ) and a sweet orange ( Citrus sinensis ). Scientific name: Citrus × clementina .
